*[[1844]] &amp;ndash; [[Jacob Aall]], Norwegian journalist and statesman (b. 1773)
*[[1859]] &amp;ndash; [[John Vianney]], French priest and saint (b. 1786)
*[[1873]] &amp;ndash; [[Viktor Hartmann]], Russian painter (b. 1834)
*[[1875]] &amp;ndash; [[Hans Christian Andersen]], Danish writer (b. 1805)
*[[1886]] &amp;ndash; [[Samuel J. Tilden]], American lawyer and politician, 25th [[Governor of New York]] (b. 1814)
*[[1900]] &amp;ndash; [[Isaac Levitan]], Russian painter (b. 1860)
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[Jules Lemaître]], French critic and dramatist (b. 1853)
*[[1919]] &amp;ndash; [[Dave Gregory (cricketer)|Dave Gregory]], Australian cricketer (b. 1845)
*[[1922]] &amp;ndash; [[Enver Pasha]], Ottoman military officer (b. 1881)
*[[1938]] &amp;ndash; [[Pearl White]], American actress (b. 1889)
*[[1941]] &amp;ndash; [[Mihály Babits]], Hungarian writer and poet (b. 1883)
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[Alberto Franchetti]], Italian composer (b. 1860)
*[[1957]] &amp;ndash; [[Washington Luís]], Brazilian politician, 13th [[President of Brazil]] (b. 1869)
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; [[Ethel Anderson]], Australian poet (b. 1883)
*[[1959]] &amp;ndash; [[József Révai]], Hungarian politician (b. 1898)
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Peter Smith (cricketer)|Peter Smith]], English cricketer (b. 1908)
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Enrique Angelelli]], Argentine bishop (b. 1923)
*  1976   &amp;ndash; [[Roy Thomson, 1st Baron Thomson of Fleet]], Canadian publisher (b. 1894)
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Melvyn Douglas]], American actor (b. 1901)
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; [[Bruce Goff]], American architect, designed the [[Boston Avenue Methodist Church]] (b. 1904)
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[Don Whillans]], English mountaineer (b. 1933)
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Nikiforos Vrettakos]], Greek writer and poet (b. 1912)
*[[1992]] &amp;ndash; [[Seichō Matsumoto]], Japanese writer and journalist (b. 1909)
*[[1993]] &amp;ndash; [[Chinmayananda]], Indian spiritual leader and teacher (b. 1916)
*  1993   &amp;ndash; [[Bernard Barrow]], American actor (b. 1927)
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Geoff Hamilton]], English gardener, broadcaster, and author (b. 1936)
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; [[Jeanne Calment]], French super-centenarian (b. 1875)
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[Yury Artyukhin]], Russian engineer and astronaut (b. 1930)
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Rodney Ansell]], Australian hunter, inspiration for ''[[Crocodile Dundee]]'' (b. 1953)
*  1999   &amp;ndash; [[Victor Mature]], American actor (b. 1913)
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[Leslie Glass (entertainer)|Leslie Glass]], American porn actress (b. 1963)
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Lorenzo Music]], American actor (b. 1937)
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Frederick Chapman Robbins]], American pediatrician and virologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1916)
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Anatoly Larkin]], Russian-American physicist (b. 1932)
*  2005   &amp;ndash; [[Iván Szabó]], Hungarian politician (b. 1934)
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Lee Hazlewood]], American singer-songwriter and producer (b. 1929)
*  2007   &amp;ndash; [[Raul Hilberg]], Austrian-American political scientist and historian (b. 1926)
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Craig Jones (motorcycle racer)|Craig Jones]], English motorcycle racer (b. 1985)
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Blake Snyder]], American screenwriter (b. 1957)
*[[2011]] &amp;ndash; [[Death of Mark Duggan|Mark Duggan]], English shooting victim (b. 1982)
*  2011   &amp;ndash; [[Naoki Matsuda]], Japanese footballer (b. 1977)
*[[2012]] &amp;ndash; [[Johnnie Bassett]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (b. 1935)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Brian Crozier]], Australian-English journalist and author (b. 1918)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Metin Erksan]], Turkish director (b. 1929)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Hanley Funderburk]], American academic (b. 1931)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Con Houlihan]], Irish journalist (b. 1925)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Bud Riley]], American football coach (b. 1925)
*  2012   &amp;ndash; [[Arnie Risen]], American basketball player (b. 1924)
