==Holidays and observances==
* Christian [[Calendar of saints|Feast Day]]:
** [[John Vianney]]
** [[Saint Sithney|Sithney]], [[patron saint]] of mad dogs
** [[August 4 (Eastern Orthodox liturgics)]]
* [[Coast Guard Day]] ([[United States|U.S.]])
* [[Cook Islands#Public holidays|Constitution Day]] ([[Cook Islands]])
* [[Johnny Cash]] Day ([[Arkansas]])
* [[Remembrance days in Slovakia|Matica Slovenská Day]] ([[Slovakia]])
* [[Public holidays in Burkina Faso|Revolution Day]] ([[Burkina Faso]])
* The first day of [[Vitoria-Gasteiz|Fiestas de la Virgen Blanca]] ([[Vitoria-Gasteiz]])
* [[National Aboriginal and Islander Children's Day]] ([[Australia]]). Celebrated on this day as it was the practice of prior Australian governments to list 4 August as the birthday of any Indigenous Australian without a listed birth date.&lt;ref&gt;Maxwell, R. &quot;Shining a light on our children&quot;, ''[[Koori Mail]]'', 8 August 2012, p. 11.&lt;/ref&gt;

